==English==

from Greek ''didaktikos'', skillful in teaching, from ''didaktos'', taught, from ''didaskein'', ''didak''-, to teach, educate

===Pronunciation===
*dī-dăkˈtĭk

===Noun===
'''didactic'''
# {{archaic}} A [[treatise]] on teaching or [[education]].

===Adjective===
'''didactic'''
# Instructive or intended to [[teach]] or [[demonstrate]], especially with regard to [[morality]].
# Excessively moralizing.
# Regarding medicine, teaching from [[textbook]]s rather than laboratory demonstration and clinical application.

